This paper is about improving the understanding of the learning process in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the information bottleneck theory, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper explores the compression of representations in neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.NE, followed by cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
